delete a line containing a pattern:
  :g/foo/d

delete all lines NOT containing pattern:
  :v/foo/d

delete all whitespace lines:
  :v/\S/d

delete all empty lines (might be covered by above, but it matches all but whitespace):
  :v/./d

ctags
  <outside> ctags -R -f path/to/tags/file
  :se tags=/path/to/tags/file
  :ta foo
  :tn = next

SCREEN
  C-a ___
      c: create
      A: rename
      d: detach
      n: next
      p: previous
      H: logfile
screen -r: reattach
 
